children.subject: Completely missed that page! You’re right, it does look like we’re forming teams after class starts.

I think a lot of people have been enrolled off the waitlist, not sure what the official method for determining it was. On the BCourses enrollment page for CS 169 (which you're probably added into), it says this:

---

Enrollment for S'19 is by “section 999”, meaning that at enrollment time you won’t have an official section. HOWEVER:

  • During the first week, we will sort into sections, taking into account preferences (see Team Formation below) and schedule conflicts.

---

So I think enrollment is just directly into the class and not based on team formation required before enrollment.

history.content: I was just enrolled off the waitlist for 169; wanted to double check that this wasn’t some sort of mistake as I haven’t heard anything about the professor deciding team formation yet.
